attendingChurch: ﻿attended by Jesuit Fathers, two at Virginia City, and two at Helena

instNote: ﻿Besides the usual branches of a solid English education, the modern languages, vocal and instrumental music, drawing, and painting are taught. Terms for board and tuition are $250 per annum. To this Institution is, moreover, attached a select day-school.

persNote: ﻿The substantial and ornamental branches of education are taught under the direction of Mother Beatrice, Prioress of the Institution. Although this Institution has been but a short time in existence, it has been favored with kind patronage of both Catholics and Protestants, owing chiefly to the energy and perseverance of the Rev. E. Hartig, Pastor of the Missions.

instNote: ﻿The girls' school is conducted by three of the Sister of Mercy. While a first-class male teacher has charge of the boys' school.
